# Coding Standards
- ALWAYS use 4 spaces for indentation in all file types (.tsx, .ts, .java, .cs, .json).
- NEVER use 2-space indentation or tabs.
- When editing existing files, if you see 2-space indentation, your priority is to convert the entire file to 4-space indentation first.
- Strictly follow this rule even if the project's default seems different, unless I explicitly say otherwise.